Reverend Emmanuel
Motolla, who was Chief Aide of His Grace, to Bishop Dr. B.E Lekganyane has
passed away. Rev Motolla served the
church and His Grace with loyalty and commitment for many decades. The African National
Congress (ANC) sent condolences to the Motolla family after learning about the
passing. ANC National
spokesperson Pule Mabe said the ANC sends its heartfelt condolences to the
Motolla family, Bishop Lekganyane, the Zion Christian Church, and the entire
religious community. ”We wish them strength
and fortitude during this difficult time,” Mabe said.